.TH "nilfs_mdt_forget_block" 9 "nilfs_mdt_forget_block" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_mdt_forget_block \- discard dirty state and try to remove the page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_mdt_forget_block
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "unsigned long block "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode of the meta data file
.IP "block" 12
block offset
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_mdt_forget_block\fP clears a dirty flag of the specified buffer, and
tries to release the page including the buffer from a page cache.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned. On error, one of the following
negative error code is returned.

-EBUSY - page has an active buffer.

-ENOENT - page cache has no page addressed by the offset.
